Add both images to the same folder, too.

Finally, run the full template game and create a guibitmapctrl in the playgui (name it "guiTextureTest" for example).
Walk the soldier to around x = 40, y = -30 (you can use localclientconnection.player.getposition() to know your location).
Then run this in the console:
`guiTextureTest.setNamedTexture("maptexture");`

A clover with the map is shown. Rotate the soldier and call again
`guiTextureTest.setNamedTexture("maptexture");`
And the map will rotate.
You could use schedules or ScriptTickObject for the update to be each frame.

